com.storytron.uber.operator

Class OperatorDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.operator.OperatorDictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Operator>

    public final class OperatorDictionary
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Operator>
    Class for handling operators and groups of them. Operators are grouped into menus.

    All dictionaries share certain common operators which are defined in the file OperatorList.xml. The method loadOperators() must be called to load the common operators before creating OperatorDictionary instances, otherwise the instance will be initially empty.

      • getOperatorMenuIndex

        public int getOperatorMenuIndex(OperatorDictionary.Menu m,
                                java.lang.String tLabel)

        Returns the index of the operator with name tLabel in the menu m. This index would be usually different from the one in the overall operator collection.

        This method is used to retrieve the indexes of operators in a menu so that they can be reordered based on the indexes (see moveOperatorMenu(com.storytron.uber.operator.OperatorDictionary.Menu, int, int)).

        The index of an operator might change anytime an operator is reordered or deleted.

        Returns:
        the index of the operator in the menu m, or -1 in case that the operator is not found in that menu.
